<dl id="n42025a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42025a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42025a"> 25(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Mary the / Egyptian</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So it is with the life of St. Mary, the Egyptian. The minute history of her life, her public scandals, her conversion, long prayers and fastings in solitude, the detailed history of her last days and of her death, all these we have; but not a single word is said of her confessing to anyone. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 120</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
